HEADWORD: male fern
<hw>male fern</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A fern of North America and Europe
(<spn>Dryopteris filix-mas</spn>) whose rhizomes and stalks yield an
oleoresin used to expel tapeworms. It is a member of the
<isa>woodfern</isa> genus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Malefic</ent>⟦br⟧
